Music & Events
Labor Day
Monday September 1st
Sunday may 8th
Come celebrate the long Labor Day weekend with us!
11:00 AM - 11:00 PM
BLUES JAM SPECTACULAR
Wednesday September 3rd
Sunday may 8th
Every Wednesday
Miami's Premiere BLUES JAM! Now running for 25 years, our Wednesday Blues Jam has become legendary! We have a core group of 4 or 5 musicians and guest musicians are invited to jump in for a song or two. You never know what can happen. We've seen it with 8 players up there including a full horn section. This is a jam you don't wanna miss!
08:30 PM - 12:00 AM
THURSDAY JAZZ JAM NIGHT
Thursday September 4th
Sunday may 8th
Every Thursday
Join us for Thursday Jazz Jam Night, where talented musicians come together for an unforgettable night of improvisation and rhythm! We have a core group of skilled players, and guest musicians are always welcome to jump in for a song or two.
From smooth solos to spontaneous collaborations, every night brings a unique jazz experience—you never know what magic will happen on stage!
08:00 PM - 11:00 PM
SOUNDS OF MIAMI Flamenco Band
Friday September 5th
Sunday may 8th
Sound of Miami is a flamenco fusion band bringing high-energy, vibrant performances perfect for Miami nights. We expect this show to be SPECTACULAR!
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
Titanic welcome's  the CRAZY TALK Band
Saturday September 6th
Sunday may 8th
Crazy Talk is a rock and country band playing a mix of new and classic rock and modern country music
CRAZY TALK BAND
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
KARAOKE Sundays!!!
Sunday September 7th
Sunday may 8th
Every Sunday
By far, Miami's most popular Karaoke event, join Karaoke Plus for an exciting night of fun, song and laughter.  This is a FREE event and is 21+ only.
08:30 PM - 12:00 AM
The JACOB GEORGE BAND
Saturday September 13th
Sunday may 8th
Based Out Of Miami, FL The Jacob George Band Sounds Like, according To Grammy Award Winner Bonnie Hayes, “Real Rock And Roll.” IndieU.Com Raves, "Throw Away Your Auto-Tuners And Drum Machines, Jacob George Is All About Organic Sound. Drawing Inspiration From The Likes Of Neil Young And Jack White, Jacob George Layers Gritty Rock Vocals Atop Rugged Folk Acoustics."
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
The return of the Rolla Coasters
Saturday September 20th
Sunday may 8th
Check out these BAD-ASS Rock-n-Rolla's.
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
The return of ANALOG Band
Saturday September 27th
Sunday may 8th
These Rockers have a playlist of very well-known songs that range from Rock to Pop, Ballads and even a few very famous Spanish Rock songs like Mana and Soda Stereo. An excellent show from professional musicians.
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
*** MAEVE ***
Saturday October 4th
Sunday may 8th
Maeve McMahon is a 22 year old singer, songwriter, and performer from Massachusetts, now based in Miami. As a genre blending artist, she mixes  pop, folk, country, and rock. This past April, Maeve released her debut EP,
Traffic Lights
on all streaming platforms!
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
Fusion / Jam from AISLE 14 Band
Saturday October 11th
Sunday may 8th
The ORIGINAL FUSION JAMBAND
FROM GAINESVILLE, FL
Aisle 14 is an Original Fusion Jamband, writing and performing music heavily inspired by Classic Country, Reggae, Psychedelic Rock, and Funk as well as new takes on standards in those genres. Based in Gainesville, FL, Aisle 14 has been performing regularly in the North Central Florida region since 2021
https://aisle14band.com/home
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
The return of the BackBeat Band
Saturday October 18th
Sunday may 8th
Classic Blues and Rock Regrooved!  https://www.facebook.com/backbeatbandmiami
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
The CHRISTOPHER DEAN BAND
Saturday October 25th
Sunday may 8th
Touring the East Coast from Maryland, this Rockin` Blues band will shake your soul and leave you begging for more!
09:00 PM - 12:00 AM
Halloween
Friday October 31st
Sunday may 8th
Bring your best costume and join us on Halloween!
11:00 AM - 12:00 AM

Saturday November 1st
Sunday may 8th
Yes, we are bringing back the ALMOST THERE Band, one of our local favorites.  They are a 4 piece "pop-rock" band from Miami,  playing great songs from the 60's thru 90's.
ALMOST THERE BAND

Saturday November 8th
Sunday may 8th
Don't miss the Titanic debut of JOE & the Southbound Band.  We are expecting a huge crowd this evening, so make your dinner reservations soon at 305-668-1742. This will be one ROCKING show!!!
